headline: 3 Consumer Stocks with Warning Signs
summary: Most consumer discretionary businesses succeed or fail based on the broader economy. Thankfully for the industry, all signs are pointing up as discretionary stocks have gained 23.9% over the past six months, beating the S&P 500’s 16.8% return.
